{
  "text": "In the DNS study of [CITATION_1] at Re τ = 180, the peak c rms−max /c max (for the central line source) was found to be 0.8 at x/h ≈ 4. This is not inconsistent with our LES data, given the possible effects of source size and Re number. Much smaller values were observed by [CITATION_2] in uniform shear turbulence. The relative intensity of the scalar fluctuations was approximately 0.5 at x/M ≈ 6 and far downstream (x/M ≈ 120) it had decreased to 0.15. [CITATION_3] estimated the asymptotic value of the relative intensity to be 0.4 in their grid turbulence experiments. Collectively, all these results suggest that the asymptotic value of c rms−max /c max is very dependent on the specific type of flow, although we emphasise that in channel (or pipe) flows it must be zero.",
  "correct_citation": {
